The paper discusses game-semantic models, which are typically used in the study of programming languages and logic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with combinatorial constraints and language operations, which are topics that fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to cs.TL (Temporal Logic) as it discusses the shape of plays. The paper also touches on the concept of the Abramsky Cube, which is related to category theory and may be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
